Ivory Coast Opposition Says 12 Were Killed, 37 Injured in Abidjan Violence

-- B y   P a u l i n e   B a x   a n d   O l i v i e r   M o n n i e r
-- 
2011-02-21T19:40:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/ivory-coast-opposition-says-12-were-killed-37-injured-in-abidjan-violence.html
At least 12 people were killed and
37 wounded in  Ivory Coast ’s commercial capital, Abidjan, today
after security forces fired on protesters, according to
statement e-mailed by the opposition coalition known as RHDP.  Seven others were left dead after fighting Feb. 19 and
yesterday, according to the statement. Troops used “grenade
launchers and hand grenades,” it added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pauline Bax in Johannesburg at 
 pbax@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emily Bowers at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net  